## 2. **Asian Options**

Asian options depend on the **average price** of the underlying asset over time.

---

### Black–Scholes (Geometric Average Only)

For **geometric average Asian options** (European-style only):

#### Adjusted Parameters:

$$
\sigma_{\text{hat}} = \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{3}}, \quad \mu_{\text{hat}} = \frac{1}{2}(r - \frac{1}{2} \sigma^2) + \frac{\sigma_{\text{hat}}^2}{2}
$$

#### Call Option:

$$
C_{\text{geo}} = e^{-rT} \left(S_0 e^{\mu_{\text{hat}} T} N(d_1) - K N(d_2)\right)
$$

#### Put Option:

$$
P_{\text{geo}} = e^{-rT} \left(K N(-d_2) - S_0 e^{\mu_{\text{hat}} T} N(-d_1)\right)
$$

Where:

$$
d_1 = \frac{\ln(S_0 / K) + (\mu_{\text{hat}} + 0.5 \sigma_{\text{hat}}^2) T}{\sigma_{\text{hat}} \sqrt{T}}, \quad d_2 = d_1 - \sigma_{\text{hat}} \sqrt{T}
$$

---

### Monte Carlo (Arithmetic Average)

#### Arithmetic Average:

$$
\bar{S} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} S_{t_i}
$$

Simulate asset paths with $n$ time steps.

#### Call Payoff:

$$
C_{\text{arith}} \approx e^{-rT} \cdot \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \max(\bar{S}^{(i)} - K, 0)
$$

#### Put Payoff:

$$
P_{\text{arith}} \approx e^{-rT} \cdot \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \max(K - \bar{S}^{(i)}, 0)
$$

