## 3. **American Options**

American options allow **early exercise** any time before expiry. No closed-form Black–Scholes solution exists (except for non-dividend-paying calls).

---

### Least-Squares Monte Carlo (LSM) – by Longstaff-Schwartz

1. Simulate multiple paths of the asset price.
2. At each time step, identify **in-the-money** paths.
3. Use regression to estimate the **expected continuation value**.
4. Compare immediate exercise vs continuation.
5. Store the optimal value at each step (i.e., perform **backward induction**).

#### Payoff at each time step:

$$
\text{Exercise value} = 
\begin{cases}
\max(S_t - K, 0) & \text{(call)} \\
\max(K - S_t, 0) & \text{(put)}
\end{cases}
$$

Final price is the discounted average of optimal payoffs.

